Are you

9
00:02:20,630 --> 00:02:21,520
a customer?

10
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,590
This is interesting.

11
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:23,800
Are you guys

12
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:25,240
not accepting any customers?

13
00:02:25,990 --> 00:02:27,710
We are.

14
00:02:27,910 --> 00:02:28,750
Please come inside.

15
00:02:35,150 --> 00:02:36,000
How long

16
00:02:36,310 --> 00:02:37,710
has this shop been operating?

17
00:02:37,710 --> 00:02:38,550
I have no idea.

18
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:40,840
Aren't you the owner?

19
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:41,680
I'm not.

20
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:43,240
He went out for some business.

21
00:02:43,250 --> 00:02:44,990
I'm just watching over
the shop on his behalf.

22
00:02:45,190 --> 00:02:46,310
Take a look around for now.

23
00:02:46,530 --> 00:02:48,030
I don't know about the prices either.

24
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:49,730
You can inquire about them
when he's back.

25
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:57,710
Isn't this a Northern Song Dynasty
Ru Ware Sky-Blue Glaze Large Dish?

26
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:02,750
There are barely 100 Northern Song Ru
ware pieces left in the world.

27
00:03:02,910 --> 00:03:04,870
How come a tiny shop like this
has one of them?

28
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,150
Is it that rare?

29
00:03:07,710 --> 00:03:09,710
But I don't see
anything special about it.

30
00:03:10,410 --> 00:03:12,190
We use the same plates
for our meals at home.

31
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:14,960
But I believe that Mister
won't sell any knockoffs.

32
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,870
People say that
the antique trade is a mixed bag.

33
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:20,870
I'm sure it's because people like you

34
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:22,800
spoiled our reputation!

35
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,590
A Northern Song Dynasty Ru Ware
Sky-Blue Glaze Large Dish?

36
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:26,680
Listen,

37
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,280
this isn't even a high-quality knockoff!

38
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:30,230
If it's genuine,
I'll swallow it in front of you!

39
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,360
Call your boss here.

40
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,560
I'll reason with him!

41
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,400
- That's not it...
- Were you looking for me?

42
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,800
Bizhi, you've finally returned.

43
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,470
He said that you sold knockoffs.

44
00:03:44,070 --> 00:03:44,910
Mr. Bi,

45
00:03:44,910 --> 00:03:46,800
I didn't know that this was your shop.

46
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:49,470
It's impossible for you
to sell knockoffs. I was plain wrong.

47
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:51,310
There are plenty of treasures here.

48
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:53,760
Some of them are so rare
that I don't even know their names.

49
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,100
Is that made of agarwood?

50
00:03:57,150 --> 00:03:58,800
It is, huh?

51
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:02,030
I was wondering about the fragrant scent
upon entering the shop.

52
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,120
This is excellent.

53
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,120
It's quite expensive.

54
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,240
No.

55
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:08,870
